The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Imphal, May 2: The Manipur government will give arms training to civilians in two villages to help defend themselves against militants.          
	The Congress governments move comes in the middle of a controversy in Chhattisgarh over Salwa Judum, a vigilante group formed to take on Maoists.          
	If successful, the Manipur model will be replicated in other parts of the state as well. Yes, the cabinet today resolved to recruit 300 volunteers from Heirok (in Thoubal district) and 200 volunteers from Chajing (in Impal West), who will be provided arms by the government, a minister said. The volunteers will be called special police officers and be given a monthly pay of Rs 3,000 each.                  
	Dhaka (PTI): Amitabh Bachchan will play Bangladesh founder Sheikh Mujibur Rahman in a Shyam Benegal film. The Poet of Politics will also star Abhishek Bachchan as the young Mujib and Aishwarya Rai Bachchan in a key role.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): An alumni association of IIMs has approached Delhi High Court to restrain the Centre from providing quota for OBC students. It argued that the government had misinterpreted the Supreme Court judgment, which had made it clear that the reservation is not available in post-graduate courses.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): Freedom fighter Nirmala Deshpande died in sleep on Thursday. She was 79. Shambhavi Mishra, 11, the daughter of a close associate, performed the last rites on Friday.                  
	Calcutta: Two seven-year-old boys were killed and several injured when a Norwester struck Bengals Nadia and Murshidabad districts on Friday evening. A tree under which boys who were playing football took shelter crashed, killing one. The other boy was killed when the tiled roof of his house caved in.                  
	 Chhapra: A Bengal jail warden was beaten to death in a Bihar village by residents who apparently mistook him for a thief. Police said Shiv Singh, 52, who was schizophrenic, was spotted walking in a village bylane on Thursday night. He was posted in Bengals Purulia district.                                                                                                                         
